1 olive oil
2 potato
1 bag baby broccoli
1 packet Lamb Shortloin
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
20 g butter
1 bag salad leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 pinch chilli flakes
1 packet basil pesto
1 cucumber
2 clove garlic
1 packet Italian Truffle Mayonnaise

Preheat the BBQ to a high heat. Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to the boil. Cut the potato into large chunks. Cook the potato in the boiling water until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes. Drain and set aside.

While the potato is cooking, trim the baby broccoli. Finely chop the garlic. Roughly chop the cucumber. In a medium bowl, combine the baby broccoli and a drizzle of olive oil, then season with salt and pepper. In a second medium bowl, combine garlic & herb seasoning with a drizzle of olive oil. Add the lamb shortloin, season, then turn to coat.

When the BBQ is hot, grill the lamb for 3-5 minutes on each side for medium-rare or cooked to your liking. Transfer to a plate, cover with foil and rest for 5 minutes.

TIP: The spice blend will char slightly, this adds to the flavour!

No BBQ? Heat a large frying pan over a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook lamb for 3-4 minutes, each side, or until cooked to your liking.

While the lamb is grilling, grill the baby broccoli until charred and tender, 3-5 minutes each side. Transfer to a large bowl and allow to cool.

No BBQ? Return the frying pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook baby broccoli until tender, 3-5 minutes each side. Transfer to a large bowl and allow to cool.

Return the saucepan to a medium heat, then cook
the butter until beginning to brown, 2-3 minutes.
Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
Remove from the heat, then return the potatoes
to the pan with the Italian truffle mayonnaise.
Season and toss to combine. To the baby broccoli,
add the salad leaves, cucumber and a drizzle of
white wine vinegar. Toss to combine.

Sprinkle a pinch of chilli flakes (if using) over the truffle mayo potatoes. Slice the lamb. Spread the basil pesto over a serving plate and top with the lamb (plus any resting juices!). Serve with the potatoes and grilled veggie rocket salad.